 Job Description
 Position Overview:
 We are on a true agile transformation journey and are looking for experienced and dedicated individuals to join us. You will have a great opportunity to work within two talented scrum teams to solve real world problems as well as to forge the role of dedicated Scrum Master within our software development department and showcase the benefits to the team and stakeholders.
 You will be part of an engineering organization that entrusts the teams to deliver various portions of our applications with lots of autonomy while receiving guidance and feedback to help them grow.
 What will you be?
 A Scrum Master that is comfortable taking the below stances as/when best appropriate:
 Servant Leader
 Ensure the team always has the end user in mind
 Help create a psychologically safe environment
 Encourage leadership in others and instill a mindset that everyone is a leader
 Teacher
 Teach others the agile manifesto and principles and the Scrum framework in detail
 Teach others the theory behind agile methodologies, engineering practices and scaling frameworks
 Keep fresh with the latest agile thought leadership and bring it back to the business
 Mentor
 Mentor teams who are new to agile and scrum
 Mentor and be mentored by other Scrum Masters
 Coach
 Be a mirror to the team - observe what's going on in the team and provide honest, constructive feedback to them
 Coach the development team and the product owner in their roles
 Facilitator
 Facilitate scrum ceremonies and other meetings within your teams
 Use facilitation and collaboration techniques and approaches to achieve effective outcomes
 Protector
 Be aware of common agile anti-patterns and work with the team to address them
 Maintain metrics that can help teams continuously improve and get teams to own and use those metrics themselves
 Impediment Remover
 Remove impediments to your scrum teams and facilitate the team to remove impediments themselves
 Be proactive in exposing hidden or unspoken impediments
 Change Agent
 Have a systems-thinking mindset to drive effective change across the organization
 Promote continuous improvement and learning within yourself, individuals, teams and across the business
 Foster an experimentation culture
 Qualifications:
 Strong communication, collaboration and facilitation skills
 A high level of emotional intelligence
 Ability to engage, influence and inspire others to adopt the agile mindset
 Experience working in an agile environment as a Scrum Master 
 Team fit and culture are very important to us. We are looking for people who are:
 Self-motivated
 Able to drive change
 Effective leaders
 Creative and innovative thinkers
 
 Basic Requirements
 3+ years of experience as a Scrum Master or similar role
 
 Travel Requirements
 
 Relocation Provided
 
 Position Type
 
